08:24.700 --> 08:27.980
One way they found was with winglets, which are those little curly bits at the end of

08:27.980 --> 08:28.980
the wing.

08:28.980 --> 08:30.900
Let's have a quick look at how they work.

08:30.900 --> 08:34.620
Winglets were introduced to decrease induced drag, which occurs when high pressure air

08:34.620 --> 08:39.320
below the wing begins to bleed over the edge into the low pressure air above.

08:39.320 --> 08:43.780
This flow creates vortices off the tips of the wing that create drag and reduce lift,

08:43.780 --> 08:46.500
which reduces the fuel economy of the plane.

08:46.500 --> 08:50.580
Winglets act to reduce these vortices by reducing the airflow over the edge of the wing.

